pull.title: [qa] Fix block message processing error in sendheaders.py

events.body:
good catch!

The `last_message["block"]` variable isn't actually used at all in this test (and `last_block` wasn't used before my refactor which introduced this bug), so we can actually just remove the `on_block()` method override entirely.
